results.definition: any foodstuff made by combining different ingredients
examples: he volunteered to taste her latest concoction
he drank a mixture of beer and lemonade

results.definition: an additional ingredient that is added by mixing with the base
examples: the growing medium should be equal parts of sand and loam with an admixture of peat moss and cow manure
paste made by a mix of flour and water
the mixing of sound channels in the recording studio
